			<div class="content" id="post-content-2022444">
									

<p>This is a collab tale and is open to those who feel inspired to add reports of their own.</p>
<p>Based off of the <a href="http://joyreactor.com/post/283033">airplane gripe sheet</a> that's floating around the internet. The reports are short, almost curt, and are humorous, though to varying degrees.</p>
<p>If you get an idea, go for it, but don't post half-baked ideas as I will edit this for quality control. If unsure, feel free to run an idea through the comments, via chat, or PM me.</p>
<p>If a post is on the fence, I may try to edit it, though others just deleted. Imagine a humorous maintenance related situation within the Foundation and try to trim it down to one sentence to describe it and one sentence to fix it.</p>
<p>tl;dr bullets for adding reports</p>
<ul>
<li>Don't force weak idea.</li>
<li>Keep the reports short. Super short.</li>
<li>Limit 10 per page. Start a new page after that.</li>
<li>New reports are to be added to the bottom of the latest page.</li>
</ul>
